subsection.p:
In the ReadingAndWriting, class, the main() method makes the connection to the server and gets the handle (i.e. a CStyxFile object) to the file on the remote server. Then it calls the setAndGetContents() method, whose contents are very simple:
file.setContents("hello JStyx world"); System.out.println(file.getContents());
Note that both setContents() and getContents can throw StyxExceptions and so we have to catch this or re-throw it from the method. If you run this code the string "hello JStyx world" should be printed out.
